= ui_row do
  = ui_col md: { num: 8 }, sm: { num: 12 }  do
    = title 'Getting Started ', display_ui: false
    .bd-callout
      %p
        %strong Important:
        Ui Bibz doesnâ€™t use webpacker anymore (No Nodejs needed).
        The librairie uses the new
        = link_to "importmap", "https://github.com/rails/importmap-rails", target: "_blank"
        solution introduced in Ruby on Rails 7.x.x.
        From now on, Ui Bibz use importmap and sprocket.

    %h2 Install

    Add these lines in your Gemfile:
    = example do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # Gemfile
          gem "ui_bibz"
    Run command:
    = example do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Terminal' do
        :plain
          bundle install

    %h2 Assets with importmap and sprocket

    Put these lines in the good place:
    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # config/importmap.rb
          ...
          pin 'ui_bibz_js', to: 'ui_bibz_js.js', preload: true
          ...

    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # app/javascript/applications.js
          ...
          import UiBibz from 'ui_bibz_js'

          let uiBibzJs = new UiBibz
          uiBibzJs.start()
          ...


    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # app/assets/stylesheets/application.sass
          ...
          @import ui_bibz
          ...

  = ui_col md: { num: 4 }, sm: { num: 12 } do
    %div
      :markdown

        ##Compatibility

        Gem is compatible with [**Ruby**](https://www.ruby-lang.org/ "Ruby") version 3.x.x and [**Ruby On Rails**](http://rubyonrails.org/ "Rails") 7.x.x.

        With __rails 7.x.x__, __Ui Bibz__ is compatible with [**hotwire**](https://hotwire.dev/ "Hotwire") and [**stimulus**](https://stimulus.hotwire.dev/ "Stimulus").

    %div
      :markdown

        ##Simple form

        Gem is compatible with [simple_form](#{ simple_form_path }).
        All inputs fields can be used with this [gem](https://github.com/plataformatec/simple_form).
